bug.short_desc: Built-in USB webcam causing 30s delay in resume from suspend, other USB errors
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1259249 dmesg showing a suspend/resume cycle
Description of problem: This notebook has a built-in USB webcam 5986:068f "BisonCam,NB Pro" with the uvcvideo driver. It can be connected/disconnected using a special keyboard combination.
With the camera attached, there is a ~30s delay when resuming from suspend-to-RAM. With it disabled, normal operation resumes immediately.
During resume with camera I get the following in dmesg:
[ 206.322736] usb 1-5-port3: cannot reset (err = -110) [ 207.346733] usb 1-5-port3: cannot reset (err = -110) [ 208.370563] usb 1-5-port3: cannot reset (err = -110) [ 209.394567] usb 1-5-port3: cannot reset (err = -110) [ 209.394575] usb 1-5-port3: Cannot enable. Maybe the USB cable is bad?
which is absent if the camera is disabled first. In either case, though, the camera still works.
In either case, I still see the following in dmesg:
[ 285.172051] xhci_hcd 0000:00:14.0: port 3 resume PLC timeout
[ 286.151005] usb 1-4:1.0: rebind failed: -517 [ 286.151011] usb 1-4:1.1: rebind failed: -517
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): kernel-4.9.12-200.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Ensure webcam is enabled. 2. Suspend to RAM. 3. Resume.
Actual results: 30s delay before screen comes back to life.
Expected results: Immediate resumption of operation, as when the camera is disabled.
Additional info: Tried usbcore.autosuspend=-1, no difference.
There's an intermittent quality to this, generally the first suspend/resume after boot is OK. The ones thereafter have variable delays.
Unbinding the xhci_hcd controller before suspend (and rebinding it after resume) helps. Wonder if this is more ACPI's thing...
